Interface AudioService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ConversationService, Observable

    public interface AudioService
extends ConversationService, Observable
    This interface controls the local audio that this endpoint sends into the conversation.

    • Field Detail

      • HOLD_PROPERTY_ID

        static final int HOLD_PROPERTY_ID
        Property ID for notifying that Hold / Resume state of the call has changed. Subscribers will be notified via the onPropertyChanged method on the Observable.OnPropertyChangedCallback interface with this property id. E.g. callback.onPropertyChanged(HOLD_PROPERTY_ID). Clients are expected to call the isOnHold method in the callback to get the changed state.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        Returns:

      • toggleMute

        void toggleMute()
         throws SFBException
        Toggle the local mute state. If the current local state is MUTED, the state will transition to UNMUTING and eventually to UNMUTED. The UNMUTING state represents notification sent to the SFB Servers of the unmute action. In case of error the state will move back to MUTED. If the current local state is UNMUTED, the state will transition to MUTED.
        Throws:
        SFBException - Exception.
